name: Alan Moore's Songbook

description:
CONTENTS:

Portrait of Author by P. Craig Russell -- Pen & Ink drawing of Neil

The Song of the Audience -- Poem original to this collection

Introduction by Neil Gaiman, August 1993 (essay)

Chivalry (w/illustration by Michael Zulli) -- short story

Nicholas Was . . . -- vignette

Babycakes -- short story along the lines of Swift's "A Modest Proposal"

Troll-Bridge (w/illustration by Charles Vess) -- short story which also appeared in the premier issue of Realms of Fantasy with an illustration by Gary Lippincott

Vampire Sestina -- poem

Webs (w/illustration by Steve Bissette) -- short story

Six to Six (w/illustration by Bill Sienkiewicz) -- "fictionalized" essay

A Prologue -- An introduction to Mary Gentle's Scholars & Soldiers (essay)

Foreign Parts - short story

Cold Colours -- poem

Luther's Villanelle -- poem

Mouse -- short story

Gumshoe -- short story

The Case of the Four & Twenty Blackbirds (w/illustration by Jill Karla Schwarz) -- short story

Virus -- poem

Looking for the Girl -- short story

Post-Mortem on Our Love -- poem

Being an Experiment Upon Strictly Scientific Lines -- "fictionalized" essay

We Can Get Them for You Wholesale -- short story

The Mystery of Father Brown -- an essay from 100 Great Detectives

Murder Mysteries (w/illustration by P. Craig Russell) -- short story later adapted into graphic novel format published by Dark Horse Press
name: Angels and Visitations

description: A promo item given during Chicago's Comic Con in 1993. Features art by many of comics top names, stories by Neil Gaiman.
name: Neil Gaiman: Guest of Honor (Ashcan)
